<p>The Community Council receives a large number of requests for financial support during the year and priority is given to charities and organisations based within and bordering the Community Council area or ones that offer services that directly benefit the community.</p>
<p>Financial requests are normally considered each February; in exceptional circumstances and where there is a time constraint, applications may be considered at other times.</p>
<p>The Community Council has given <strong>financial donations</strong> to the following organisations during the 2017-18 financial year:</p>
<p>Carmarthen and District Youth Opera, The Royal British Legion Poppy Appeal, Gwyl Y Goeden Salem, Y Lloffwr, Cruse Bereavement Care, Urdd Gobaith Cymru Sir Gar, Carmarthenshire Federation of Young Farmer’s Clubs,  Macmillan Cancer Support , Cancer Information and Support Services, Llandeilo Young Farmers Club, Cylch Meithrin Ffairfach, Tenovus Cancer Care, Children’s Wales Air Ambulance and Llandeilo and District Sports Association.</p>
